                "rel": 0.001
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "h2o2_pathway_isolated_298K",
          "description": "H2O2 pathway in isolation at 298 K (p_CO2=40 Pa, p_SO2=0.001 Pa, p_H2O2=1.01325e-4 Pa, Fe_III=Mn_II=0, p_O3=0). R_O3 and R_FeMn are zero; R_total = R_H2O2 only. H2O2 is highly soluble (H_H2O2≈987 mol/m³/Pa) giving H2O2_aq≈0.1 mol/m³. The H⁺ from charge balance (0.01279 mol/m³, pH≈4.89) enters the H2O2 rate law Eq. 7.84: R_H2O2 = k·[H⁺]·[H2O2]·[HSO3⁻]/(1+K·[H⁺]).",
          "parameter_overrides": {
